Yeah, murph overheard the a.d.a
and the social worker talking.

605
00:34:18,009 --> 00:34:21,009
Medical records have
confirmed their mom had cancer,

606
00:34:21,037 --> 00:34:24,417
Nobody wants to press charges,
but lockin' up the neighbor?

607
00:34:24,468 --> 00:34:25,478
It was the ghost.

608
00:34:25,494 --> 00:34:28,514
Yeah, but they could
charge amy with a crime.

609
00:34:29,116 --> 00:34:30,866
Try her as an adult.

610
00:34:30,887 --> 00:34:33,237
She's here.

611
00:34:33,261 --> 00:34:36,021
- Can you give me a second?
- Yeah.

612
00:34:37,497 --> 00:34:39,267
They're splitting them up!

613
00:34:39,287 --> 00:34:43,427
Henry's going to some foster home,
while amy and lisa are being detained.

614
00:34:43,463 --> 00:34:44,483
I knew it!

615
00:34:44,509 --> 00:34:47,569
This is what happens to
families when both parents die!

616
00:34:47,598 --> 00:34:51,498
You can't control their lives anymore, and
every time you do, you just make it worse.

617
00:34:51,532 --> 00:34:54,982
The best thing that you can do is just help
them understand what's happening to them.

618
00:34:55,023 --> 00:34:57,143
You're the one who doesn't understand!

619
00:34:57,166 --> 00:35:00,576
You keep saying that,
but understand what?

620
00:35:00,607 --> 00:35:03,387
What is it that you're not telling me?

621
00:35:03,414 --> 00:35:07,344
Because you're afraid of something, and
it has nothing to do with the county.

622
00:35:08,494 --> 00:35:11,334
Or is itsomeone?

623
00:35:11,362 --> 00:35:15,092
Is it someone who'd
get them when you died?

624
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:21,390
I need to talk to the
officer who found henry.

625
00:35:21,423 --> 00:35:22,383
Sure, what's up?

626
00:35:22,399 --> 00:35:25,229
This ghost is hiding a
lot more than her death.

627
00:35:25,256 --> 00:35:26,866
OK

628
00:35:29,371 --> 00:35:33,091
she kept saying she knew this would
happen, the kids would get torn apart.

629
00:35:33,124 --> 00:35:34,984
Officer: actually, the country
prefers to keep siblings together.

630
00:35:35,005 --> 00:35:36,405
Where was she getting her information?

631
00:35:36,424 --> 00:35:40,994
Well, that's what i was wondering, but then
it made me think, what if she has someone?

632
00:35:41,031 --> 00:35:46,351
A sibling who is in foster care or
adopted, someone that the kids never knew?

633
00:35:46,394 --> 00:35:49,524
You're talking about family
services records. They're sealed.

634
00:35:49,553 --> 00:35:51,793
Come on. Not for you.

635
00:35:51,817 --> 00:35:53,177
Please.

636
00:35:53,205 --> 00:35:57,095
That little boy had everything to
lose when he came to you for help.

637
00:35:57,622 --> 00:36:00,922
He's lost so much already.

638
00:36:09,645 --> 00:36:12,025
Hi, are you tracy edmondson?

639
00:36:12,049 --> 00:36:13,089
Yes.

640
00:36:13,126 --> 00:36:15,196
My name is melinda gordon.

641
00:36:15,249 --> 00:36:17,769
I knew your sister karen.

642
00:36:17,814 --> 00:36:20,604
My sister?

643
00:36:24,786 --> 00:36:27,986
There's so many questions. I...

644
00:36:28,318 --> 00:36:32,568
I'm not honestly sure i
want to know the answers.

645
00:36:32,604 --> 00:36:35,044
She had 3 children.

646
00:36:35,069 --> 00:36:38,089
Their father died,
too. They have no one.

647
00:36:40,612 --> 00:36:42,942
You didn't know that, did you?

648
00:36:42,967 --> 00:36:46,147
You're not one of the people
she asked to take care of them.

649
00:36:46,176 --> 00:36:49,056
She probably figured i'd say no.

650
00:36:49,084 --> 00:36:52,714
Because you didn't take
her when your parents died?

651
00:36:53,490 --> 00:36:55,840
I know about the accident.

652
00:36:55,885 --> 00:36:59,165
I know that you were
19 when you lost them.

653
00:36:59,195 --> 00:37:02,945
You were old enough
to take over custody.

654
00:37:04,286 --> 00:37:10,136
I sat in a courtroom while the judge
asked her over and over if she wanted me.

655
00:37:10,181 --> 00:37:15,561
She cried every night until
she passed out from exhaustion.

656
00:37:15,614 --> 00:37:17,124
And they were my parents, too.

657
00:37:17,154 --> 00:37:18,234
I could barely function.

658
00:37:18,250 --> 00:37:20,500
How was i supposed to
fix her broken heart?

659
00:37:20,524 --> 00:37:24,054
I don't think anyone
expected you to do that.

660
00:37:24,086 --> 00:37:25,326
Except maybe you.

661
00:37:25,353 --> 00:37:28,723
Well, it's too late now. She's gone.

662
00:37:29,700 --> 00:37:33,970
What if it wasn't too
late just meet her kids.

663
00:37:34,006 --> 00:37:35,906
They're really...

664
00:37:35,927 --> 00:37:38,797
Really self sufficient and loving.

665
00:37:38,825 --> 00:37:42,255
And they need you to be their family.

666
00:37:42,990 --> 00:37:45,010
Legally, it's the only
way they can stay together.

667
00:37:45,033 --> 00:37:47,373
She is a complete stranger to them.

668
00:37:47,417 --> 00:37:49,347
I'm not their family.

669
00:37:49,369 --> 00:37:53,969
If karen were here, she'd
tell you i'm not her family.

670
00:37:54,007 --> 00:37:55,457
I gave up that right.

671
00:37:55,476 --> 00:37:57,756
Listen to her. She's right.

672
00:37:57,780 --> 00:37:59,690
So...

673
00:38:00,245 --> 00:38:04,385
I can't. I don't...

